          <avActivityHighlights>Wet and gliding snow require caution.</avActivityHighlights>
          <avActivityComment>In particular in east to north to west facing aspects more medium-sized gliding avalanches and wet snow slides are possible especially in starting zones where no previous releases have taken place.</avActivityComment>
          <snowpackStructureComment>Below approximately 1800 m only a little snow is lying. In gullies and bowls at high altitude there is still a very large amount of snow. The spring-like weather conditions gave rise to significant settling of the snowpack. Backcountry tours should be started and concluded early.</snowpackStructureComment>
